1) First compile the PingServer.java file using javac PingServer.java in the command prompt
2) Then execute the server program using java PingServer 10002 12 
3) Here the numbers given through the command are the command line arguments , first one is the port number and the second is the optinal argument seed
4) Now in the another command prompt or on the another machine compile the PingClient.java file using javac PingServer.java in the command prompt
5) Then execute the client program using java ClientServer atria 10002 , here the atria is the server name and the 10002 is the server port.
6) Now you can see the desired output at client side and server side.
